ğŸ§  Understanding: Application Server vs Web Server
Web Server:

Handles HTTP requests and responses.

Serves static files (HTML, CSS, JS, images).

Examples: Nginx, Apache.

Application Server:

Runs application logic (Python, Node.js, etc).

Connects to databases, handles dynamic content.

Examples: Gunicorn, uWSGI, Node.js runtime, Django/Flask app server.

Together:

A user makes a request â†’ web server receives it â†’ forwards dynamic requests to the app server â†’ app server processes logic â†’ returns response â†’ web server sends it back to the user.

